<h2 class="bac">Our Business:</h2>
<p class="bac">
   Do the details interest you as much as the big picture? As an analyst in our Research group, you&#39;ll work with both as you help to cover large and small companies in a specific industry or an industry sector. You will gather, analyze, and interpret financial data but always in a broader context so you can provide not just information, but insight as well. That&#39;s how you add value. 
</p>
<p class="bac">
   The groups focusing on quantitative research within the Research division include the equity derivatives, interest rate derivatives, commodity strategy, credit and structured credit research groups. These groups produce client-driven quantitative research in some of the fastest growing areas in the global financial markets. 
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Overview:</h2>  
<p class="bac">
   This programme is for you if you are pursuing a doctoral degree with a quantitative focus and you have an interest in working in the financial services industry. We offer a variety of opportunities for final year doctoral students who have high-level mathematical skills and the desire to use them in a fast-paced, demanding business environment. 
</p>
<p class="bac">
   You will find that your academic background in research and quantitative analysis is applicable to real world problems in several business areas, particularly Research. The combination of highly quantitative work and an intense level of interaction with colleagues will create a unique professional challenge and career path for you. 
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Qualifications:</h2>
<ul class="bac">	
	<li>Excellent degree/PhD in a mathematical or financial discipline </li>	
	<li>Excellent communication skills </li>	
	<li>Strong problem solving and analytical skills </li>	
	<li>Strong quantitative background </li>	
	<li>Ability to think creatively </li>	
	<li>Familiarity with programming </li>
</ul>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Training:</h2>
<p class="bac">
   We offer a bespoke development programme unique to our quantitative hires which runs throughout the year.  A modular based approach is used to develop skills and behaviors required to succeed in your role and to further progress your career. 
</p>
<p class="bac">
   The program includes: 
</p>
<ul class="bac">	
	<li>Strategic overview of the bank, focusing on the debt and equity businesses</li>	
	<li>Sessions covering topics including how to add value through your seat and communicating with impact</li>	
	<li>Opportunities to interact and network with peers </li>	
	<li>A mentoring program </li>
</ul>

